org.foxlabs.validation.converter

Interface Converter<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - The type of value to be converted
    All Superinterfaces:
    Validation<V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConverter, ArrayConverter, BigDecimalConverter, BigIntegerConverter, BooleanConverter, ByteConverter, CharacterConverter, ClassConverter, CollectionConverter, ConverterMessageWrapper, ConverterWrapper, CustomConverter, DateConverter, DoubleConverter, EnumConverter, FileConverter, FloatConverter, IntegerConverter, LocaleConverter, LogLevelConverter, LongConverter, MapConverter, NumberConverter, NumberConverter.DecimalType, NumberConverter.IntegerType, SequenceConverter, ShortConverter, SimpleTokenizer, StringConverter, TimeZoneConverter, Tokenizer, UnsupportedConverter, URIConverter, URLConverter

    public interface Converter<V>
extends Validation<V>
    The root interface in the converter hierarchy. A converter provides ability to convert values of certain data type into and from string representation. Converter instances should be registered and obtained from ConverterFactory.
    Author:
    Fox Mulder
    See Also:
    ConverterFactory

      • decode

        <T> V decode(String value,
             ValidationContext<T> context)
        Converts string representation of value into object.

        The method ValidationContext.isLocalizedConvert() determines if converter should take locale into account. Locale can be obtained through the method ValidationContext.getMessageLocale().

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of validated entity.
        Parameters:
        value - String representation of value.
        context - Validation context.
        Returns:
        Decoded value.
        Throws:
        MalformedValueException - if conversion fails.

      • encode

        <T> String encode(V value,
                  ValidationContext<T> context)
        Converts value into string representation.

        The method ValidationContext.isLocalizedConvert() determines if converter should take locale into account. Locale can be obtained through the method ValidationContext.getMessageLocale().

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of validated entity.
        Parameters:
        value - Value to be encoded.
        context - Validation context.
        Returns:
        String representation of value.
